# /.github/CODEOWNERS
#
# Authoritative review-ownership map for dq-platform.
# Format: GitHub CODEOWNERS — last matching rule wins.
# Path-rule shape committed by ADR-0015 (B1-9, 2026-05-22) and
# preserved structurally by ADR-0057 (single-user CODEOWNERS
# amendment, 2026-05-30). Under the single-user model committed
# by ADR-0057, every rule names @FabioCaffarello (personal user
# that owns the repository); the prior @PLACEHOLDER-org/...
# group identifiers collapsed when the org-creation session was
# declared structurally out-of-scope.
#
# Deployment precondition per ADR-0057 §Consequence 7: the
# GitHub branch-protection rule "Require review from CODEOWNERS"
# MUST be off (or self-approval must be enabled), because the
# only listed owner is also every PR's author.
#
# The path-rule structure (general-to-specific ordering;
# explicit-line duplications for /.github/workflows/,
# /docs/adr/, etc.) is preserved as future-org-migration
# substrate per ADR-0057 §Consequence 10.

# --- Default ------------------------------------------------------
*                                       @FabioCaffarello

# --- Engine workspace ---------------------------------------------
/engine/                                @FabioCaffarello

# --- Tools workspace ----------------------------------------------
/tools/                                 @FabioCaffarello

# --- Rules workspace (asymmetric per ADR-0001 §C3) ----------------
# Default: domain teams own per-entity rule YAMLs.
/rules/                                 @FabioCaffarello

# Override: schema mirror is platform-team only (byte-equal copy of
# engine/internal/dsl/schema/, never hand-edited per ADR-0001 §2).
/rules/_schema/                         @FabioCaffarello

# Override: owner metadata is platform-team only (ADR-0006 §9 second
# line of defense — "no alert without owner" enforcement).
/rules/_owners.yaml                     @FabioCaffarello
/rules/_owners.schema.json              @FabioCaffarello

# --- Deploy workspace (per-environment depth per B1-4 MD-3) -------
/deploy/                                @FabioCaffarello
/deploy/base/                           @FabioCaffarello
/deploy/overlays/local/                 @FabioCaffarello
/deploy/overlays/qa/                    @FabioCaffarello
/deploy/overlays/prod/                  @FabioCaffarello

# --- Docs ---------------------------------------------------------
# /docs/adr/ kept as an explicit line (same owner as /docs/) so a
# future ADR-specific reviewer group can be slotted in without
# editing /docs/.
/docs/                                  @FabioCaffarello
/docs/adr/                              @FabioCaffarello

# --- Multi-agent contract (ADR-0009 §1–§3) ------------------------
# Single authorship for CLAUDE.md (source) and the two pointers,
# so /sync-agents drift cannot be approved without the canonical
# contract being touched.
/CLAUDE.md                              @FabioCaffarello
/AGENTS.md                              @FabioCaffarello
/.claude/                               @FabioCaffarello
/.codex/                                @FabioCaffarello

# --- CI + branch protection (ADR-0001 §C9, ADR-0008) --------------
# /.github/workflows/ and /.github/CODEOWNERS kept as explicit
# overrides (same owner as /.github/) so a future workflows-only or
# CODEOWNERS-only reviewer group can be slotted in without editing
# /.github/.
/.github/                               @FabioCaffarello
/.github/workflows/                     @FabioCaffarello
/.github/CODEOWNERS                     @FabioCaffarello

# --- Root build/runtime config ------------------------------------
/Makefile                               @FabioCaffarello
/go.work                                @FabioCaffarello
/go.work.sum                            @FabioCaffarello
/docker-compose.yml                     @FabioCaffarello
/scripts/                               @FabioCaffarello

# --- Studies (reasoning history, R8) ------------------------------
/studies/                               @FabioCaffarello
